Create SSIS Packages 8

Go to Visual Studio:

·        Create the packages in the below screenshot as follows:

2.      While creating the first package right click on the canvas and select Variables to create variables for the first package as in below screenshot:


a        ArchiveJsonData: Create a folder where you want the source files archived once loaded.  Provide this folder as the value for this variable. In my case – C:\Top\ITTrain\DA\SampleJson\TestArc\

b        JSON_FileName: Provide an initial name for the JSON file source as the value for this variable

c        JSONFilePath: Provide the full path including the name of the first file in the folder for the source file(s).  In this case I provided value as C:\Top\ITTrain\DA\SampleJson\TestData\CraigsList20200514.JSON

d        New_FileName: Press the ellipsis (…) sign marked in red to build a value for this dynamic variable so that once a file has been loaded the name will be changed as per my liking.  For example, I am adding a leading string, “Arc_” to the original file name before moving the file to the archive folder

e        Vehicle_Count: A variable for counting records loaded.  I am initializing it with value 0


The variables will make the DW dynamic and used in the first package to initialize the Foreach Loop container while capturing audit and log information and archiving the source files.
